== 1. ⚖️ Legal Foundations ==
The formal structure that guarantees our independence and neutrality.

* 🔗 **[[Legal Framework>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Legal Framework.WebHome]]**: Our Swiss Association status and IP strategy.
* 🔗 **[[Open Source Model and Licensing>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Open Source Model and Licensing.WebHome]]**: How we use code and data licenses to protect the public interest.
* 🔗 **[[Contributor License Agreement (CLA)>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.CLA.WebHome]]**: How we manage contributions to the project.

== 2. 📜 Public Policies ==
Our commitments to the users and the public.

* 🔗 **[[Privacy Policy>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Privacy-Policy]]**: How we process and protect user data under Swiss/EU law.
* 🔗 **[[Transparency Policy>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Transparency-Policy]]**: Our promise of open decision-making and auditable data.
* 🔗 **[[Terms of Service>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Terms-of-Service]]**: The agreement for using the FactHarbor platform.
* 🔗 **[[Security Policy>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Security-Policy]]**: Incident response and vulnerability reporting.

== 3. 💰 Financial Governance ==
Ensuring long-term sustainability without compromising our mission.

* 🔗 **[[Finance and Compliance>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Finance and Compliance.WebHome]]**: Non-profit budgeting and reporting.
* 🔗 **[[Large Donations Policy>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Large Donations Policy.WebHome]]**: Protecting our independence from external influence.
* 🔗 **[[Reimbursable Expenses>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Reimbursable Expenses.WebHome]]**: Our public transparency ledger for costs.

